text: Honolulu County is a county in the U.S. state of Hawaii. It contains the island of Oʻahu and several minor islands, including all of the Northwestern Hawaiian Islands (islands beyond Niʻihau) except Midway Atoll. As of the 2020 census, 1,016,508 people lived there. The county seat is Honolulu. Honolulu County was founded in 1907. ==References== Category:1900s establishments in Hawaii Category:1907 establishments in the United States Category:Hawaii counties
